: \"They were putting in work to beat Americans at facilities that were created to help Americans win.\", \"from\": 1695, \"to\": 1793, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"work\", \"from\": 1716, \"to\": 1720}, {\"ngram\": \"Americans\", \"from\": 1729, \"to\": 1738}, {\"ngram\": \"facilities\", \"from\": 1742, \"to\": 1752}, {\"ngram\": \"Americans\", \"from\": 1779, \"to\": 1788}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Both Marchand and McIntosh are prohibitive favorites in the 400 IM and gold-medal contenders in multiple other events (the exact number remains to be seen, depending on how many they decide to swim).\", \"from\": 1795, \"to\": 1994, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1813, \"end\": 1821, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/McIntosh_Laboratory\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.438583513050301e-19, \"text\": \"McIntosh\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/McIntosh_Laboratory\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/McIntosh_Laboratory\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Both Marchand\", \"from\": 1795, \"to\": 1808}, {\"ngram\": \"prohibitive favorites\", \"from\": 1826, \"to\": 1847}, {\"ngram\": \"the 400 IM and gold-medal contenders\", \"from\": 1851, \"to\": 1887}, {\"ngram\": \"multiple other events\", \"from\": 1891, \"to\": 1912}, {\"ngram\": \"the exact number\", \"from\": 1914, \"to\": 1930}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Marchand arrives as arguably the biggest home-country hero of the Olympics.\", \"from\": 1995, \"to\": 2070, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Marchand\", \"from\": 1995, \"to\": 2003}, {\"ngram\": \"the biggest home-country hero\", \"from\": 2024, \"to\": 2053}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 2057, \"to\": 2069}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But by the end, the Summer Games could be the Games of Summer.\", \"from\": 2071, \"to\": 2133, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the end\", \"from\": 2078, \"to\": 2085}, {\"ngram\": \"the Summer Games\", \"from\": 2087, \"to\": 2103}, {\"ngram\": \"the Games\", \"from\": 2113, \"to\": 2122}, {\"ngram\": \"Summer\", \"from\": 2126, \"to\": 2132}]}, {\"sentence\": \"They represent the two-edged opportunity that is inherent in the U.S. swimming machine.\", \"from\": 2135, \"to\": 2222, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the two-edged opportunity\", \"from\": 2150, \"to\": 2175}, {\"ngram\": \"the U.S. swimming machine\", \"from\": 2196, \"to\": 2221}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s the best place on the planet to excel at the sport, which is why it draws so much international talent\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094then that international talent disperses to home countries and tries to break the machine.\", \"from\": 2223, \"to\": 2425, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"It\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s the best place\", \"from\": 2223, \"to\": 2244}, {\"ngram\": \"the planet\", \"from\": 2248, \"to\": 2258}, {\"ngram\": \"the sport\", \"from\": 2271, \"to\": 2280}, {\"ngram\": \"so much international talent\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094then\", \"from\": 2304, \"to\": 2339}, {\"ngram\": \"home countries\", \"from\": 2379, \"to\": 2393}, {\"ngram\": \"the machine\", \"from\": 2413, \"to\": 2424}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The inherent conflict is not new, nor is it isolated to swimming.\", \"from\": 2427, \"to\": 2492, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The inherent conflict\", \"from\": 2427, \"to\": 2448}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The best basketball players from across the globe flock to the U.S. for prep, college and NBA opportunities (though they rarely come back to beat the Stars and Stripes come Olympic time).\", \"from\": 2493, \"to\": 2680, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2583, \"end\": 2586, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Basketball_Association\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.5284320813665995e-21, \"text\": \"NBA\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Basketball_Association\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Basketball_Association\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The best basketball players\", \"from\": 2493, \"to\": 2520}, {\"ngram\": \"the globe flock\", \"from\": 2533, \"to\": 2548}, {\"ngram\": \"the U.S.\", \"from\": 2552, \"to\": 2560}, {\"ngram\": \"the Stars\", \"from\": 2639, \"to\": 2648}, {\"ngram\": \"Stripes\", \"from\": 2653, \"to\": 2660}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The same could be said in many other sports.\", \"from\": 2681, \"to\": 2725, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"many other sports\", \"from\": 2707, \"to\": 2724}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But the international invasion at the very top end has never been this pronounced in the pool.\", \"from\": 2727, \"to\": 2821, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the international invasion\", \"from\": 2731, \"to\": 2757}, {\"ngram\": \"the very top end\", \"from\": 2761, \"to\": 2777}, {\"ngram\": \"the pool\", \"from\": 2812, \"to\": 2820}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This appears to be the first Olympics in which male and female swimmers with legitimate claims to being the best in the world simultaneously were trained in the U.S. but compete for foreign nations.\", \"from\": 2822, \"to\": 3020, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the first Olympics\", \"from\": 2841, \"to\": 2859}, {\"ngram\": \"legitimate claims\", \"from\": 2899, \"to\": 2916}, {\"ngram\": \"the world\", \"from\": 2938, \"to\": 2947}, {\"ngram\": \"the U.S.\", \"from\": 2979, \"to\": 2987}, {\"ngram\": \"foreign nations\", \"from\": 3004, \"to\": 3019}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cI don\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t think that\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s happened before,\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d says Joel Shinofield, managing director of sport development for USA Swimming.\", \"from\": 3022, \"to\": 3148, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3135, \"end\": 3147, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/USA_Swimming\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"USA Swimming\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/USA_Swimming\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/USA_Swimming\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Joel Shinofield\", \"from\": 3075, \"to\": 3090}, {\"ngram\": \"managing director\", \"from\": 3092, \"to\": 3109}, {\"ngram\": \"sport development\", \"from\": 3113, \"to\": 3130}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cEspecially when they\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099re competing against some of our top swimmers.\", \"from\": 3149, \"to\": 3221, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cEspecially when they\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099re\", \"from\": 3149, \"to\": 3177}, {\"ngram\": \"our top swimmers\", \"from\": 3204, \"to\": 3220}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But this is a story as old as time\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094we have some of the best coaches in the world, and we\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099re the world leader in both higher-ed and swimming.\", \"from\": 3222, \"to\": 3366, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a story\", \"from\": 3234, \"to\": 3241}, {\"ngram\": \"time\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094we\", \"from\": 3252, \"to\": 3261}, {\"ngram\": \"the best coaches\", \"from\": 3275, \"to\": 3291}, {\"ngram\": \"the world\", \"from\": 3295, \"to\": 3304}, {\"ngram\": \"we\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099re\", \"from\": 3310, \"to\": 3317}, {\"ngram\": \"the world leader\", \"from\": 3318, \"to\": 3334}, {\"ngram\": \"both higher-ed\", \"from\": 3338, \"to\": 3352}, {\"ngram\": \"swimming\", \"from\": 3357, \"to\": 3365}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Those two things draw people here.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d Marchand and McIntosh have company.\", \"from\": 3367, \"to\": 3441, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3406, \"end\": 3414, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brad_Marchand\", \"score\": 0.9999999953206498, \"rank\": 4.679267326923714e-09, \"text\": \"Marchand\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q11774891\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brad_Marchand\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Br